Serves 4Difficulty: Easy, 30 minutesPudding:75g flourPinch of salt7.5ml (1 tsp) baking powder30ml (2 tbsp) cocoa powder45g caster sugar100ml milk150ml coffee liqueur45ml (3 tbsp) melted butter1 large egg5ml (1 tsp) vanilla extract50g dark chocolate, roughly choppedSauce:90g soft brown sugar15ml (1 tbsp) cocoa200ml boiling water Just desserts: Oh-so-simple chocolate potsMethod:1. Preheat the oven to 180 C. Grease 4 x 250ml-capacity ramekins.2. Sift the flour, salt, baking powder and cocoa into a bowl. Stir in the caster sugar.3. In a separate bowl, whisk the milk, liqueur, butter, egg and vanilla, then add to the dry ingredients and beat until smooth.4. Fold in the chocolate and spoon the mixture into the ramekins. Place on a baking tray.5. For the sauce, mix the sugar and cocoa and spoon on top of each pudding.6. Pour the boiling water over the puddings and bake for 15 minutes until the tops are firm.7. Remove the puddings from the oven and let them cool for about 5 minutes. This will also allow the sauce to settle. Sprinkle with icing sugar if desired and serve with ice cream, cream or coffee liqueur.Visit http://heinstirred.com for more of Hein van Tonder's recipes.